The paper analyzes the category structure of the Universal Decimal Classification (UDC) system and Wikipedia, focusing on the category of "Arts." This involves analyzing the emerging structure of category-links and comparing it to the structure of classes in the UDC. This study involves information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL) as it looks at the categorization of information. It also involves social computing (SI) as it compares the structure of categories created socially (Wikipedia) to those created formally (UDC). Additionally, it could fall under human-computer interaction (HC) as it looks at how users interact with and navigate through information categories. Finally, it could also fall under computational linguistics (CL) as it involves analyzing the language and structure of categories.
